Recursion can be understood using the Fibonacci sequence. A recursive function to calculate it would look like this:
```python
def fib(n):
    if n <= 1: return n
    else:
        return fib(n-1) + fib(n-2)
```
This function calls itself to build up each value until it reaches the base cases. It's a perfect illustration of how a complex process breaks down into simpler parts.
